03/04/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Italian Army chief Admiral Giampaolo di Paola voiced full support for the military reform process in Bulgaria, during a meeting with his Bulgarian counterpart, General Nikola Kolev, in Sofia on Monday (3 April). The two met after Paola arrived on a three-day official visit to the Balkan country. They discussed the importance of bilateral co-operation in terms of regional and international security. Paola will also be holding talks with Bulgarian Defence Minister Vesselin Bliznakov and the head of the Bulgarian Parliament's Defence Commission, Angel Naydenov. (BNR, Bulgarian Government Web site - 03/04/06)
